A suspect who incidentally shot and killed his father, who was allegedly fighting his mom during a domestic violence incident on February 18, briefly appeared before the Belfast Magistrates Court, in Mpumalanga, and was granted bail of R1 000, Mpumalanga News reports. It is alleged the suspect found his father assaulting his mother and carrying a knife in his hands at about 3pm on Saturday when he and his siblings were returning home from a school concert. READ MORE: Talking in sleep reveals killer In an attempt to protect his mother, the suspect took his father s revolver from a cabinet and shot him in his chest. The father was declared dead on the scene. Belfast police arrested the deceased s son in connection with the murder, and investigations are still ongoing. Caxton News Service For more news your way, follow The Citizen on Facebook and Twitter.